claim.claim-text:
1. In a MIMO communication system, a method for allocating MIMO communication resources of a portable MIMO communication system, the method comprising:
determining a first set of MIMO communication resources of a portable MIMO communication system to utilize for communicating a first portion of a unit of information from the portable MIMO communication system to a MIMO communication network in a MIMO transmission, where the unit of information is a quantifiable amount of related information;
allocating the first set of MIMO communication resources for communicating the first portion of the unit of information;
determining a second set of MIMO communication resources of the portable MIMO communication system to utilize for communicating a second portion of the unit of information from the portable MIMO communication system to the MIMO communication network in a MIMO transmission, a portion of the second set of MIMO communication resources being different from the first set of MIMO communication resources, a portion of the second set of MIMO communication resources overlapping with the first set of MIMO communication resources; and
allocating the second set of MIMO communication resources for communicating the second portion of the unit of information.

21. In a MIMO communication system, a sub-system for allocating MIMO communication resources of a portable MIMO communication system, the sub-system comprising at least one module that operates to:
determine a first set of MIMO communication resources of a portable MIMO communication system to utilize for communicating a first portion of a unit of information from the portable MIMO communication system to a MIMO communication network in a MIMO transmission, where the unit of information is a quantifiable amount of related information;
allocate the first set of MIMO communication resources for communicating the first portion of the unit of information;
determine a second set of MIMO communication resources of the portable MIMO communication system to utilize for communicating a second portion of the unit of information from the portable MIMO communication system to the MIMO communication network in a MIMO transmission, a portion of the second set of MIMO communication resources being different from the first set of MIMO communication resources, a portion of the second set of MIMO communication resources overlapping with the first set of MIMO communication resources; and
allocate the second set of MIMO communication resources for communicating the second portion of the unit of information.

35. In a MIMO communication system, a method for allocating MIMO communication resources, the method comprising:
determining a first set of MIMO communication resources of a portable MIMO communication system to utilize for communicating a first portion of a telephone conversation from the portable MIMO communication system to a MIMO communication network in a MIMO transmission;
allocating the first set of MIMO communication resources for communicating the first portion of the telephone conversation from the portable MIMO communication system to the MIMO communication network;
determining a second set of MIMO communication resources of the portable MIMO communication system to utilize for communicating a second portion of the telephone conversation from the portable MIMO communication system to the MIMO communication network in a MIMO transmission, at least a portion of the second set of MIMO communication resources being different from the first set of MIMO communication resources, at least a portion of the second set of MIMO communication resources being the same as the first set of MIMO communication resources; and
allocating the second set of MIMO communication resources for communicating the second portion of the telephone conversation from the portable MIMO communication system to the MIMO communication network.
